  "prompt": "What is more likely to happen than Donald Trump becoming president?",
  "response": "Predicting political outcomes can be uncertain and speculative. However, based on various factors such as polling data, public opinion, legal matters, and historical precedents, it is possible to evaluate some events that might be statistically more probable than Donald Trump becoming president. These could include:\n\n1. Another major political figure or celebrity entering the presidential race.\n2. Significant changes or reforms happening within a political party.\n3. Greater advancements in technology, such as widespread adoption of AI or electric vehicles.\n4. Continued economic fluctuations influencing elections.\n5. International developments impacting global politics more heavily.\n\nUltimately, while political predictions can be insightful, they should be approached with caution and an understanding of the fluid nature of political landscapes.",
